{"TopicId":156600,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Making a rocket to beat all other rockets","CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-02-17T18:44:56Z","PageNum":10,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"KAL 9000","CreatedById":140704,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-07T14:11:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/84978-alpha-tech/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002284978\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/84978-alpha-tech/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@alpha tech\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0How big is the satellite you\u0027re planning on building?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKeep in mind, dude, Earth is a lot bigger than Kerbin.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Low Kerbin Orbit, you\u0027re going at ~2,300 m/s.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Low Earth Orbit, it\u0027s ~8,000 m/s.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo take a KSP rocket and scale up the Delta-V in it\u00A0by that much.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat should give you the Delta-V you need.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-07T14:12:13Z\u0022 title=\u002203/07/2017 02:12  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 7, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by KAL 9000\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-07T14:15:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222978523\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488895882\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022140704\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KAL 9000\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, KAL 9000 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/84978-alpha-tech/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002284978\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/84978-alpha-tech/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@alpha tech\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0How big is the satellite you\u0027re planning on building?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKeep in mind, dude, Earth is a lot bigger than Kerbin.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Low Kerbin Orbit, you\u0027re going at ~2,300 m/s.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn Low Earth Orbit, it\u0027s ~8,000 m/s.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo take a KSP rocket and scale up the Delta-V in it\u00A0by that much.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat should give you the Delta-V you need.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is why I need a very efficient first stage to de the heavy lifting and then a second stage to kick it near orbital velocity and a third stage to finalize it and I need to figure antenna to work this out for communication\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-07T15:51:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222978494\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488894033\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI need one where I can test ideas on and a proto type\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStatic tests\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222978494\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488894033\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso is not that I don\u0027t care about safety it\u0027s just that if it comes to my attention that something is dangerous I will take precautions\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is why documentation is needed. If something is dangerous but you don\u0027t know or think it is, you could be killed. You tell us what your going to do\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Ein depth\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0then we would be able to point it out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222978494\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488894033\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd I also need a list of fuels that I could try and mix different than kno3 and sugar.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know this sounds rude\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eit is\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cu\u003ENOT\u00A0\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E supposed to. \u00A0You can do that yourself. Only use sources you find credible. Also, posting links to the research you have done is part of documentation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222977944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488835085\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022munlander1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, munlander1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also think you should join a rocketry forum\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo have you made any progress here?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222978494\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488894033\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif I bring the thrust chamber to a fine point and expand it for the gas will it produce a higher thrust\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think you are thinking\u00A0of making a nozzle. One of the problems here is the exhaust velocity. You have to get it has close to the atmospheric pressure at that altitude. That is why in a vacuum the most efficient nozzle is an infinity large one. Since your rockets will be flying around normal atmospheric pressure, you will end up with a much shorter nozzle. Similar to the space shuttle\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Solid fuel Rocket Booster\u0022\u003Esrb\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222978525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221488896151\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is why I need a very efficient first stage to de the heavy lifting and then a second stage to kick it near orbital velocity and a third stage to finalize it and I need to figure antenna to work this out for communication\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou are a\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cem\u003Elong\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0way from here. I would not worry about that stage right now at all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-07T18:39:00Z\u0022 title=\u002203/07/2017 06:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 7, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by munlander1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAuto correction fail\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T21:37:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni think I have\u00A0a problem how can I get the rocket to go straight up without going off coarse too much cause I live near a lot of trees\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T00:15:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222983732\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489354673\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni think I have\u00A0a problem how can I get the rocket to go straight up without going off coarse too much cause I live near a lot of trees\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuy\u00A0any rocket off\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.estesrockets.com/rockets/launch-sets\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis list\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0and appropriate motors for the rocket. Please provide proof of purchase (receipt, the rocket, etc.).\u00A0Once you buy one you don\u0027t have to get another launch stand (that is if you don\u0027t want another).\u00A0They sell rockets\u00A0without launch stands also. Follow the directions and local regulations before you launch. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GDJ","CreatedById":58462,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T02:02:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis thread has to be a giant joke on everybody.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T15:59:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK I have a concept for finding how I need to make the rocket by calculating the volume and density of the fuel and the density of the container by the volume to get the mass of the stage and all I have to do to is repeat this and add the last stages mass and by the burn rate of propellant and mass to acommadate for stage. this is only a theroy I haven\u0027t figured it all out yet and I need an approximation of the Delta v I need to achieve this orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0 \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/168560-munlander1/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022168560\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/168560-munlander1/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@munlander1\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour thoughts on this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:02:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984272\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489420742\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfinding how I need to make the rocket\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan you explain this more?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:16:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK if I know my Delta v I came do approximations on how I need to build the stages of my rocket by calculating fuel mass burn rate etc\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:20:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984283\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489421807\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK if I know my Delta v I came do approximations on how I need to build the stages of my rocket by calculating fuel mass burn rate etc\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can\u0027t calculate delta v before you design your rocket. That\u0027s like finding a car\u0027s mpg before designing it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:26:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo the Delta v to get to orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:37:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can use that to get an ideal of how I need to separate the Delta v over 3 stages and then I build the rocket calculating the mass of the fuel and the volume needed to get the Delta v and the density/volume for the container for the fuel and the payload and all other parts that are unlisted.\u00A0 And I can repeat this for all other stages but adding the mass of the previous stages\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:39:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984302\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489423031\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can use that to get an ideal of how I need to separate the Delta v over 3 stages and then I build the rocket calculating the mass of the fuel and the volume needed to get the Delta v and the density/volume for the container for the fuel and the payload and all other parts that are unlisted.\u00A0 And I can repeat this for all other stages but adding the mass of the previous stages\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I mean I guess that could work but that is really only for orbital space flight. Right now, I don\u0027t think you should be worried about that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:40:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984303\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489423144\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022munlander1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, munlander1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, I mean I guess that could work but that is really only for orbital space flight. Right now, I don\u0027t think you should be worried about that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s ok I can tone it down to work with smaller rockets\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:41:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984306\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489423218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s ok I can tone it down to work with smaller rockets\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, you would have to have a specific \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003Edv\u003C/abbr\u003E in mind. You would also have to take drag and other forces into account.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:42:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDelta v required to hit the edge of the atmosphere? And for drag and stuff just add more Delta v to last stage 100m/s maybe?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-13T16:47:21Z\u0022 title=\u002203/13/2017 04:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 13, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by alpha tech\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:47:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984310\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489423369\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDelta v required to hit the edge of the atmosphere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1.4 km/s it looks like. You can google this stuff. Technically, you would be still in the atmosphere if you cross the karman line at 100km. But to do that, you would have to measure your motor in pounds. I think one rocket\u0027s motor was 16 pounds. That means lots of paper work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-13T16:52:28Z\u0022 title=\u002203/13/2017 04:52  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 13, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by munlander1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Terwin","CreatedById":139655,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:49:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984310\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489423369\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDelta v required to hit the edge of the atmosphere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDelta-v needed for launch operations is highly dependent on your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E. \u00A0If your have a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E of 20, then you need a lot less d-v to get to the same height than if you have a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1.001, and if your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E is \u0026lt; 1, you will not get anywhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou will also need to account for drag once you have got a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E \u0026gt; 1, but I am not familiar enough with the math to know how much of an impact drag\u00A0will have on your required d-v budget.(I just know that it is enough to justify fairings for everything that is not already reasonably aerodynamic)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T16:55:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984313\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489423623\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022munlander1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, munlander1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no idea. Technically, you would be still in the atmosphere if you cross the karman line at 100km. But to do that, you would have to measure your motor in pounds. I think one rocket\u0027s motor was 16 pounds. That means lots of paper work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell orbital velocity is about 17500 mph so I think the x15 went about 5000 MPH\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984316\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489423779\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139655\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Terwin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Terwin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand it got into space where you could feel no gravity\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984316\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489423779\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139655\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Terwin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Terwin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDelta-v needed for launch operations is highly dependent on your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E. \u00A0If your have a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E of 20, then you need a lot less d-v to get to the same height than if you have a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1.001, and if your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E is \u0026lt; 1, you will not get anywhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou will also need to account for drag once you have got a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E \u0026gt; 1, but I am not familiar enough with the math to know how much of an impact drag\u00A0will have on your required d-v budget.(I just know that it is enough to justify fairings for everything that is not already reasonably aerodynamic)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will take this Into consideration\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T17:00:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984320\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489424100\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand it got into space where you could feel no gravity\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there was no gravity it would stay there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T17:02:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984322\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489424421\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022munlander1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, munlander1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf there was no gravity it would stay there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was on suborbital trajectory but pilots experienced zero g\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T17:04:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984324\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489424525\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was on suborbital trajectory but pilots experienced zero g\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell gravitational fire I defined by mass and distance. You are being pulled by everything in the universe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut back to rockets! So when do you plan to buy the rockets?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"alpha tech","CreatedById":84978,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T17:06:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhenever I get more money.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"peadar1987","CreatedById":81207,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T17:06:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984324\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489424525\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002284978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022alpha tech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, alpha tech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt was on suborbital trajectory but pilots experienced zero g\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell technically anything in freefall you\u0027re experiencing zero g. Hit a bump hard enough in a car and you\u0027ll experience zero g for a second.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"munlander1","CreatedById":168560,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-13T17:07:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222984329\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022156600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221489424799\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002281207\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022peadar1987\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, peadar1987 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell technically anything in freefall you\u0027re experiencing zero g. Hit a bump hard enough in a car and you\u0027ll experience zero g for a second.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is only at apogee and only for seconds though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}